#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:140
msgid "Showing Emails in HTML or Plain Text Format"
msgstr "Showing Emails in HTML or Plain Text Format"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:142
msgid ""
"You can view email messages in two formats, HTML, or plain text. HTML "
"messages can have text formatting, numbering, bullets, colored "
"backgrounds, and links, which can make messages easier to read. Plain "
"text messages can always be read by other email clients. Plain text does "
"not support any text formatting, styles, links, or images. You can view a"
" message in plain-text mode even if it contains HTML. The HTML tags are "
"displayed in the body of the message in the plain text view."
msgstr ""
"You can view email messages in two formats, HTML, or plain text. HTML "
"messages can have text formatting, numbering, bullets, colored "
"backgrounds, and links, which can make messages easier to read. Plain "
"text messages can always be read by other email clients. Plain text does "
"not support any text formatting, styles, links, or images. You can view a"
" message in plain-text mode even if it contains HTML. The HTML tags are "
"displayed in the body of the message in the plain text view."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:147
msgid "Under Displaying Messages, click on the Display mail field."
msgstr "Under Displaying Messages, click on the Display mail field."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:148
msgid "From the drop-down menu, select **As HTML** or **As text**."
msgstr "From the drop-down menu, select **As HTML** or **As text**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:152
msgid "Configuring Read Receipts Behavior"
msgstr "Configuring Read Receipts Behavior"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:154
msgid ""
"When sending messages to other |product| users, you can choose to request"
" a return receipt, which notifies you when the recipient opens your "
"email. However, for this feature to function, the recipient must have the"
" read receipt feature enabled or manually accept it as soon as they open "
"the email."
msgstr ""
"When sending messages to other |product| users, you can choose to request"
" a return receipt, which notifies you when the recipient opens your "
"email. However, for this feature to function, the recipient must have the"
" read receipt feature enabled or manually accept it as soon as they open "
"the email."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:156
msgid "To enable the read receipt feature:"
msgstr "To enable the read receipt feature:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:160
msgid "Under **Receiving Messages**, click on the **Read Receipt** field."
msgstr "Under **Receiving Messages**, click on the **Read Receipt** field."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:161
msgid "Select **Always send a read receipt**."
msgstr "Select **Always send a read receipt**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:164
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can choose the option **Never send a read receipt** to"
" ensure it is never sent automatically or select **Ask me** so that you "
"are prompted each time you open an email with a read receipt request, "
"giving you the choice to send it or not."
msgstr ""
"Alternatively, you can choose the option **Never send a read receipt** to"
" ensure it is never sent automatically or select **Ask me** so that you "
"are prompted each time you open an email with a read receipt request, "
"giving you the choice to send it or not."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:171
msgid "Setting Up Email Filters"
msgstr "Setting Up Email Filters"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:173
msgid ""
"You can effectively manage your inbox by utilizing email filters. These "
"filters allow you to set up actions, such as organizing incoming and "
"outgoing emails into specific folders."
msgstr ""
"You can effectively manage your inbox by utilizing email filters. These "
"filters allow you to set up actions, such as organizing incoming and "
"outgoing emails into specific folders."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:175
msgid ""
"A filter consists of specific conditions paired with corresponding "
"actions."
msgstr ""
"A filter consists of specific conditions paired with corresponding "
"actions."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:177
msgid ""
"When an email satisfies the specified conditions, the designated actions "
"are triggered."
msgstr ""
"When an email satisfies the specified conditions, the designated actions "
"are triggered."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:179
msgid ""
"Conditions can encompass various criteria, such as the subject, sender, "
"or date of the email."
msgstr ""
"Conditions can encompass various criteria, such as the subject, sender, "
"or date of the email."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:180
msgid "Actions may include moving, tagging, or redirecting the emails."
msgstr "Actions may include moving, tagging, or redirecting the emails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:182
msgid "Some examples are:"
msgstr "Some examples are:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:184
msgid ""
"Automatically moving incoming emails into designated folders. For "
"instance, emails from your supervisor can be automatically routed to your"
" \"Management Directives\" folder upon arrival."
msgstr ""
"Automatically moving incoming emails into designated folders. For "
"instance, emails from your supervisor can be automatically routed to your"
" \"Management Directives\" folder upon arrival."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:185
msgid ""
"Tag specific emails for easy identification. For example, emails from the"
" corporate events mailing list can be labeled with an \"Events\" tag."
msgstr ""
"Tag specific emails for easy identification. For example, emails from the"
" corporate events mailing list can be labeled with an \"Events\" tag."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:186
msgid ""
"Redirect or delete emails based on predefined criteria. For instance, all"
" emails from a specific sender can be forwarded or moved to the Trash "
"folder."
msgstr ""
"Redirect or delete emails based on predefined criteria. For instance, all"
" emails from a specific sender can be forwarded or moved to the Trash "
"folder."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:187
msgid "Assign importance flags to specific emails."
msgstr "Assign importance flags to specific emails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:189
msgid ""
"Filters are applied sequentially, following the order in which they are "
"listed in your settings. You retain the flexibility to modify the order "
"of filters as needed."
msgstr ""
"Filters are applied sequentially, following the order in which they are "
"listed in your settings. You retain the flexibility to modify the order "
"of filters as needed."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:192
msgid "Creating a Filter"
msgstr "Creating a Filter"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:198
msgid "You can configure filters independently for incoming and outgoing emails."
msgstr "You can configure filters independently for incoming and outgoing emails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:200
msgid "To create a filter for **incoming** or **outgoing emails**:"
msgstr "To create a filter for **incoming** or **outgoing emails**:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:204
msgid ""
"Under **Filters**, choose either **Incoming Message Filters** or "
"**Outgoing Message Filters** depending on whether you intend to create a "
"filter for emails you receive or emails you send, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Under **Filters**, choose either **Incoming Message Filters** or "
"**Outgoing Message Filters** depending on whether you intend to create a "
"filter for emails you receive or emails you send, respectively."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:205
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:264
msgid "Click **CREATE**. A new window appears."
msgstr "Click **CREATE**. A new window appears."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:206
msgid ""
"Insert a name for your filter in the **Filter Name** field (e.g., junk "
"mail)"
msgstr ""
"Insert a name for your filter in the **Filter Name** field (e.g., junk "
"mail)"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:207
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:266
msgid ""
"Ensure to mark the **Active filter** checkbox so the filter becomes "
"operational immediately upon its creation."
msgstr ""
"Ensure to mark the **Active filter** checkbox so the filter becomes "
"operational immediately upon its creation."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:208
msgid ""
"Under the **Conditions** section, select the proper options for the logic"
" of your filter. Press the + button if you need to add more conditions "
"(please refer to the section below titled **How to create conditions** "
"for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."
msgstr ""
"Under the **Conditions** section, select the proper options for the logic"
" of your filter. Press the + button if you need to add more conditions "
"(please refer to the section below titled **How to create conditions** "
"for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:209
msgid ""
"Under the **Actions** section, choose the appropriate action to be taken "
"if the filter conditions are met. Press the **+** button if you need to "
"add more actions (please refer to the section below titled **How to "
"create actions** for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."
msgstr ""
"Under the **Actions** section, choose the appropriate action to be taken "
"if the filter conditions are met. Press the **+** button if you need to "
"add more actions (please refer to the section below titled **How to "
"create actions** for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:210
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:274
msgid ""
"Check or uncheck the **Do not process additional filters** checkbox to "
"determine whether this filter rule, when its conditions are met, will "
"prevent the execution of any other rules. Enabling this option means that"
" once this filter’s conditions are satisfied, the system will not "
"evaluate any other filters."
msgstr ""
