#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:282
msgid "Activating/Deactivating a Filter"
msgstr "Activating/Deactivating a Filter"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:284
msgid ""
"When creating a filter, you have the option to mark the **Active filter**"
" checkbox. If selected, your filter will be placed in the Active Filters "
"section; otherwise, it will be listed under **Available Filters**."
msgstr ""
"When creating a filter, you have the option to mark the **Active filter**"
" checkbox. If selected, your filter will be placed in the Active Filters "
"section; otherwise, it will be listed under **Available Filters**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:286
msgid ""
"Active Filters are operational and will be applied to emails "
"automatically. Conversely, filters kept in the Available Filters section "
"are inactive but can be retained for future use. You have the flexibility"
" to move them into the Active Filters section whenever needed."
msgstr ""
"Active Filters are operational and will be applied to emails "
"automatically. Conversely, filters kept in the Available Filters section "
"are inactive but can be retained for future use. You have the flexibility"
" to move them into the Active Filters section whenever needed."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:288
msgid ""
"To move a filter from the Active Filters to the Available Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to deactivate and click on the **REMOVE** "
"button. This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters "
"section, where it will remain inactive until reactivated."
msgstr ""
"To move a filter from the Active Filters to the Available Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to deactivate and click on the **REMOVE** "
"button. This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters "
"section, where it will remain inactive until reactivated."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:289
msgid ""
"To move a filter from the Available Filters to the Active Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to activate and click on the **ADD** button. "
"This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters section, "
"where it will remain active until deactivated."
msgstr ""
"To move a filter from the Available Filters to the Active Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to activate and click on the **ADD** button. "
"This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters section, "
"where it will remain active until deactivated."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:292
msgid "Applying a Filter to Existing Emails"
msgstr "Applying a Filter to Existing Emails"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:294
msgid ""
"Active Filters are automatically applied to new emails, whereas for "
"managing existing emails, you may need to manually apply a filter. For "
"instance, you can create a filter to move all emails containing the word "
"'Violence' into the junk folder to tidy up your inbox."
msgstr ""
"Active Filters are automatically applied to new emails, whereas for "
"managing existing emails, you may need to manually apply a filter. For "
"instance, you can create a filter to move all emails containing the word "
"'Violence' into the junk folder to tidy up your inbox."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:296
msgid ""
"This manual application allows you to organize existing emails according "
"to your preferences."
msgstr ""
"This manual application allows you to organize existing emails according "
"to your preferences."

