#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:416
msgid "Configure a CalDAV Client"
msgstr "Configure a CalDAV Client"

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:418
msgid ""
"Adding a |product| calendar to your favourite CalDAV client is "
"straightforward and requires only a few steps. The procedure is almost "
"identical on any client; in the box at the end of this section we mention"
" which are the differences."
msgstr ""
"Adding a |product| calendar to your favourite CalDAV client is "
"straightforward and requires only a few steps. The procedure is almost "
"identical on any client; in the box at the end of this section we mention"
" which are the differences."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:423
msgid ""
"In this scenario, the user *john.smith@example.com* wants to configure in"
" Mozilla's Thunderbird a calendar called *Calendar* on the domain "
"*mail.example.com*. In the remainder, replace these values with suitable "
"ones."
msgstr ""
"In this scenario, the user *john.smith@example.com* wants to configure in"
" Mozilla's Thunderbird a calendar called *Calendar* on the domain "
"*mail.example.com*. In the remainder, replace these values with suitable "
"ones."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:428
msgid "Step 1.  New Calendar"
msgstr "Chọn Lịch."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:430
msgid ""
"On your client, go to the Calendar and select **New Calendar...**. Choose"
" **On the Network**"
msgstr ""
"On your client, go to the Calendar and select **New Calendar...**. Choose"
" **On the Network**"

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:437
msgid "Step 2."
msgstr "Step 2."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:439
msgid ""
"Provide the **Username** and the **Location**, which has format "
"``https://<domain>/dav/username``, so "
"*https://mail.example.com/dav/john.smith@example.com*"
msgstr ""
"Provide the **Username** and the **Location**, which has format "
"``https://<domain>/dav/username``, so "
"*https://mail.example.com/dav/john.smith@example.com*"

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:448
msgid "Step 3."
msgstr "Step 3."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:450
msgid "You will be then presented a list, from which to choose *Calendar*."
msgstr "You will be then presented a list, from which to choose *Calendar*."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:452
msgid "You are now done! the calendar will show up in the list of your client."
msgstr "You are now done! the calendar will show up in the list of your client."

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:458 ../../contacts/toc.rst:353
msgid "Other clients"
msgstr "Other clients"

#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:460
msgid ""
"CalDAV is a standard protocol and therefore the data required to set up a"
" client are a username, an URL, and the name of a calendar. The only "
"difference is that some client requires that the calendar's name be part "
"of the URL, so you might need to provide "
"*https://mail.example.com/dav/john.smith@example.com/Calendar* as the "
"URL."
msgstr ""
"CalDAV ist ein Standardprotokoll, daher benötigen Sie für die Einrichtung"
" eines Clients einen Benutzernamen, eine URL und den Namen eines "
"Kalenders. Der einzige Unterschied besteht darin, dass einige Clients den"
" Kalendernamen in die URL einbinden müssen, sodass Sie ggf. "
"*https://mail.example.com/dav/john.smith@example.com/Calendar* als URL "
"angeben."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:7
msgid "Working with Chats"
msgstr "Lavorare con Chats"

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:14
msgid ""
"In the |product| web client, Chats serve as a key communication feature, "
"supporting both individual and group interactions. Users benefit from "
"centralized messaging, promoting real-time conversations and fostering "
"collaboration. Whether it's about sharing information, brainstorming, or "
"organizing tasks, Chats offer a seamless platform for efficient teamwork."
" Notifications ensure that users stay updated and engaged, maintaining "
"productivity whether they are working remotely or in the office."
msgstr ""
"In the |product| web client, Chats serve as a key communication feature, "
"supporting both individual and group interactions. Users benefit from "
"centralized messaging, promoting real-time conversations and fostering "
"collaboration. Whether it's about sharing information, brainstorming, or "
"organizing tasks, Chats offer a seamless platform for efficient teamwork."
" Notifications ensure that users stay updated and engaged, maintaining "
"productivity whether they are working remotely or in the office."

