"histories. Simply enter a keyword, select a result, and jump directly to "
"the corresponding message, which is visually highlighted for easier "
"reference."
msgstr ""
"Message Search allows you to quickly find specific messages, dates, or "
"content in any conversation without needing to scroll through long chat "
"histories. Simply enter a keyword, select a result, and jump directly to "
"the corresponding message, which is visually highlighted for easier "
"reference."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:250
msgid "How It Works"
msgstr "How It Works"

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:252
msgid ""
"A search icon is available in the header of every conversation. Clicking "
"it opens a search panel on the right side of the interface. Type your "
"keyword (for example, *meeting*) and press **Enter** or click the "
"**Search** button. All messages containing the keyword are displayed in a"
" chronological list, with the most recent results shown first."
msgstr ""
"A search icon is available in the header of every conversation. Clicking "
"it opens a search panel on the right side of the interface. Type your "
"keyword (for example, *meeting*) and press **Enter** or click the "
"**Search** button. All messages containing the keyword are displayed in a"
" chronological list, with the most recent results shown first."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:256
msgid "Key Features"
msgstr "Key Features"

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:258
msgid ""
"**Smart Highlighting** The searched keyword is highlighted in bold using "
"the primary color. Partial matches are also highlighted (e.g., searching "
"for *meet* highlights only that part inside *meeting*), making results "
"easier to scan."
msgstr ""
"**Smart Highlighting** The searched keyword is highlighted in bold using "
"the primary color. Partial matches are also highlighted (e.g., searching "
"for *meet* highlights only that part inside *meeting*), making results "
"easier to scan."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:261
msgid ""
"**Jump to Context** Selecting a result automatically scrolls the "
"conversation to the exact message, which is highlighted for visibility. "
"If you scroll away, simply click the result again to return—results "
"remain clickable at all times."
msgstr ""
"**Jump to Context** Selecting a result automatically scrolls the "
"conversation to the exact message, which is highlighted for visibility. "
"If you scroll away, simply click the result again to return—results "
"remain clickable at all times."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:264
msgid ""
"**Responsive Behavior** On smaller screens, the search interface adapts "
"seamlessly to ensure easy navigation without losing context."
msgstr ""
"**Responsive Behavior** On smaller screens, the search interface adapts "
"seamlessly to ensure easy navigation without losing context."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:267
msgid ""
"**Quick Iterations** To start a new search, use the backspace button to "
"clear the current query without closing the panel."
msgstr ""
"**Quick Iterations** To start a new search, use the backspace button to "
"clear the current query without closing the panel."

#: ../../chat/toc.rst:270
msgid ""
"This feature significantly improves navigation within chats, letting you "
"find information in seconds instead of manually searching through entire "
"conversations."
msgstr ""
"This feature significantly improves navigation within chats, letting you "
"find information in seconds instead of manually searching through entire "
"conversations."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:7
msgid "Composing Emails"
msgstr "Composizione di email"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:9
msgid ""
"In this section, you will discover how to navigate |product| email "
"composer and how to use its various features including working with "
"attachments, addressing emails, using account personas, etc."
msgstr ""
"Navigate the |product| email composer and use features such as "
"attachments, addressing, and account personas."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:12 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:67
msgid "Composing a New Email"
msgstr "Composing a New Email"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:14
msgid "Below is a concise summary of the steps to write and send an email:"
msgstr "Below is a concise summary of the steps to write and send an email:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:16
msgid "Select the **Mails** feature from your left sidebar."
msgstr "Select the **Mails** feature from your left sidebar."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:17
msgid ""
"Click on the **NEW** button located on the top bar. A new compose board "
"will appear."
msgstr ""
"Click on the **NEW** button located on the top bar. A new compose board "
"will appear."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:18
msgid "Enter recipient email addresses in the *To* field."
msgstr "Inserire gli indirizzi email dei destinatari nel campo *A*."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:19
msgid "Optionally, add recipients to the *Cc* or *Bcc* fields."
msgstr "Optionally, add recipients to the *Cc* or *Bcc* fields."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:20
msgid ""
"Choose your email **identity/persona** (if you have more than one) from "
"the top left corner of the composing board."
msgstr ""
"Choose your email **identity/persona** (if you have more than one) from "
"the top left corner of the composing board."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:21
msgid "Write a brief subject in the *Subject* field."
msgstr "Write a brief subject in the *Subject* field."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:22
msgid "Compose your message in the body."
msgstr "Comporre il messaggio nel corpo."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:23
msgid "Click the **SEND** button to send the email."
msgstr "Fare clic sul pulsante **INVIA** per inviare l'email."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:25
msgid "A copy of the sent email is stored in your Sent folder."
msgstr ""
"Una copia dell'email inviata viene archiviata nella cartella Posta "
"inviata."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:31
msgid ""
"The Visual Cue feature displays a clear placeholder label when emails are"
" sent with only CC or BCC recipients and no direct 'To' recipients, "
"improving message visibility and recipient understanding."
msgstr ""
"The Visual Cue feature displays a clear placeholder label when emails are"
" sent with only CC or BCC recipients and no direct 'To' recipients, "
"improving message visibility and recipient understanding."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:33
msgid ""
"This feature enhances email clarity by providing immediate visual "
"information about recipient types, helping you better understand how "
"messages were distributed. To identify emails with empty 'To' fields:"
msgstr ""
"This feature enhances email clarity by providing immediate visual "
"information about recipient types, helping you better understand how "
"messages were distributed. To identify emails with empty 'To' fields:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:36
msgid "Look for the [Empty 'To' Field] label in your message list"
msgstr "Look for the [Empty 'To' Field] label in your message list"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:37
msgid "Open any email showing this placeholder to view details"
msgstr "Open any email showing this placeholder to view details"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:38
msgid "The same label will appear in the message displayer for confirmation"
msgstr "The same label will appear in the message displayer for confirmation"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:39
msgid "Use this visual cue to understand the email's recipient distribution"
msgstr "Use this visual cue to understand the email's recipient distribution"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:42
msgid "Disabling / Enabling Rich Text Editor"
msgstr "Disabling / Enabling Rich Text Editor"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:44
msgid ""
"To toggle the rich text editor on or off while using the compose board, "
"simply:"
msgstr ""
"To toggle the rich text editor on or off while using the compose board, "
"simply:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:46
msgid "Click on the three vertical dots."
msgstr "Click on the three vertical dots."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:47
msgid ""
"Choose either **Disable rich text editor** or **Enable rich text editor**"
" from the menu."
msgstr ""
"Choose either **Disable rich text editor** or **Enable rich text editor**"
" from the menu."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:49
msgid ""
"On the other hand, enabling the rich text editor can be beneficial when "
"you want to create visually appealing emails with formatting options like"
" bold, italics, underline, font colors, and font sizes. It allows you to "
"customize the appearance of your emails to make them more engaging and "
"professional-looking. Additionally, the rich text editor often provides "
"tools for inserting images, creating lists, and adjusting text alignment,"
" which can enhance the overall presentation of your email and improve "
"readability. Disabling the rich text editor can be useful when you want "
"to compose emails with plain text only, without any formatting such as "
"bold, italics, or color changes. This can help send simple, "
"straightforward messages without any distractions or potential "
"compatibility issues across different email clients."
msgstr ""
"On the other hand, enabling the rich text editor can be beneficial when "
"you want to create visually appealing emails with formatting options like"
" bold, italics, underline, font colors, and font sizes. It allows you to "
"customize the appearance of your emails to make them more engaging and "
"professional-looking. Additionally, the rich text editor often provides "
"tools for inserting images, creating lists, and adjusting text alignment,"
" which can enhance the overall presentation of your email and improve "
"readability. Disabling the rich text editor can be useful when you want "
"to compose emails with plain text only, without any formatting such as "
"bold, italics, or color changes. This can help send simple, "
"straightforward messages without any distractions or potential "
"compatibility issues across different email clients."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:54
msgid "Addressing Emails"
msgstr "Addressing Emails"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:56
msgid ""
"The autocomplete function assists you while typing in the To, Cc, and Bcc"
" fields of a new message by suggesting names from your contacts. It "
"generates a list of potential addresses where either the first name, last"
" name, or email address matches the text you have typed."
msgstr ""
"La funzione di autocompletamento ti aiuta durante la digitazione nei "
"campi A, Cc e Bcc di un nuovo messaggio suggerendo nomi dai tuoi "
"contatti. Genera un elenco di indirizzi potenziali in cui il nome, il "
"cognome o l'indirizzo email corrisponde al testo che hai digitato."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:58
msgid ""
"As you continue typing, the list of suggested addresses narrows down, "
"reflecting fewer matches available. If there are no matches in your "
"contact list or your company’s employee address list, the list "
"disappears."
msgstr ""
"As you continue typing, the list of suggested addresses narrows down, "
"reflecting fewer matches available. If there are no matches in your "
"contact list or your company’s employee address list, the list "
"disappears."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:60
msgid ""
"For instance, if you are composing an email to Sarah Johnson, whose email"
" is sarah.johnson@example.com, and you start typing \"S\" the "
"autocomplete might display:"
msgstr ""
"For instance, if you are composing an email to Sarah Johnson, whose email"
" is sarah.johnson@example.com, and you start typing \"S\" the "
"autocomplete might display:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:62 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:68
#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:73
msgid "Samuel Adams sam.adams@example.com"
msgstr "Samuel Adams sam.adams@example.com"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:63 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:69
msgid "Sarah Johnson sarah.johnson@example.com"
msgstr "Sarah Johnson sarah.johnson@example.com"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:64
msgid "Susan Lee susanlee@email.com"
msgstr "Susan Lee susanlee@email.com"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:66
msgid "If you then type \"a\" (Sa), the list will update to:"
msgstr "If you then type \"a\" (Sa), the list will update to:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:71
msgid ""
"Continuing with our example, if you proceed to type \"m\" (Sam), the "
"autocomplete list would further narrow down to:"
msgstr "Continuando con il"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:75
msgid ""
"This real-time refinement allows for a quick and efficient selection of "
"recipients based on the characters you input, ensuring accuracy and ease "
"of use in addressing your email messages."
msgstr ""
"This real-time refinement allows for a quick and efficient selection of "
"recipients based on the characters you input, ensuring accuracy and ease "
"of use in addressing your email messages."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:77
msgid ""
"To include additional recipients in either the *copy* or *blind copy* "
"sections of your email, just click on the **CC** or **BCC** buttons to "
"reveal their respective fields."
msgstr ""
"To include additional recipients in either the *copy* or *blind copy* "
"sections of your email, just click on the **CC** or **BCC** buttons to "
"reveal their respective fields."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:79
msgid ""
"Additionally, you can utilize the **drag-and-drop** feature to "
"effortlessly move email addresses from the To field to the Cc or Bcc "
"fields while composing your message. To do so, simply click and hold on "
"an address bubble and drag it to the desired field."
msgstr ""
"Additionally, you can utilize the **drag-and-drop** feature to "
"effortlessly move email addresses from the To field to the Cc or Bcc "
"fields while composing your message. To do so, simply click and hold on "
"an address bubble and drag it to the desired field."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:81
msgid ""
"You can also copy-paste email addresses directly into the To, CC, and BCC"
" fields, while composing an email: furthermore, a small contextual menu "
"appears when you right-click in the To, CC, or BCC fields, so you can "
"directly click \"Paste\" to insert email adresses, you previously copied,"
" in the related fields."
msgstr ""
"You can also copy-paste email addresses directly into the To, CC, and BCC"
" fields, while composing an email: furthermore, a small contextual menu "
"appears when you right-click in the To, CC, or BCC fields, so you can "
"directly click \"Paste\" to insert email adresses, you previously copied,"
" in the related fields."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:88
msgid "Attachments"
msgstr "Allegati"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:90
msgid ""
"Attachments play a crucial role in enhancing the effectiveness of email "
"communication by allowing users to include supplementary files such as "
"documents, images, videos, or spreadsheets along with their messages. "
"Below, you will discover various actions you can take with attachments "
"while composing an email."
msgstr ""
"Attachments play a crucial role in enhancing the effectiveness of email "
"communication by allowing users to include supplementary files such as "
"documents, images, videos, or spreadsheets along with their messages. "
"Below, you will discover various actions you can take with attachments "
"while composing an email."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:93 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:142
msgid "Adding Attachments"
msgstr "Aggiunta di allegati"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:95
msgid ""
"You can attach any file from your computer or |product| Files by using "
"the **paperclip** icon inside the composing board."
msgstr ""
"Attach any file from your computer or |product| Files via the "
"**paperclip** icon in the compose window."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:97
msgid "Adding attachment from your computer:"
msgstr "Adding attachment from your computer:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:99 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:107
msgid "Click on the paperclip icon."
msgstr "Click on the paperclip icon."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:100
msgid "Select Add from local."
msgstr "Select Add from local."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:101
msgid "A new window appears, and you can select desired files from your computer."
msgstr "A new window appears, and you can select desired files from your computer."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:103
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can simply drag a file from your computer to the "
"composing board to add it as an attachment to your email."
msgstr ""
"Alternatively, you can simply drag a file from your computer to the "
"composing board to add it as an attachment to your email."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:105
msgid "Adding attachment from your |product| Files:"
msgstr "Aggiungere un file dal computer"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:108
msgid "Select Add from Files."
msgstr "Select Add from Files."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:109
msgid ""
"A new window appears, and you can select desired files from your "
"|product| Files."
msgstr "A new window opens to select files from your |product| Files."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:111
msgid ""
"It is important to note that computer viruses are commonly transmitted "
"through file attachments. As a precaution, system administrators may "
"block incomin cdg emails containing certain types of attachments, "
"particularly those with extensions such as .EXE or .ZIP as part of their "
"filename. If you send an email to someone whose email system blocks these"
" attachments, you may not receive any notification about the blocking. "
"Therefore, it is advisable to confirm with your recipient whether they "
"have received the attachment or not."
msgstr ""
"It is important to note that computer viruses are commonly transmitted "
"through file attachments. As a precaution, system administrators may "
"block incomin cdg emails containing certain types of attachments, "
"particularly those with extensions such as .EXE or .ZIP as part of their "
"filename. If you send an email to someone whose email system blocks these"
" attachments, you may not receive any notification about the blocking. "
"Therefore, it is advisable to confirm with your recipient whether they "
"have received the attachment or not."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:118
msgid "Managing Large Attachments"
msgstr "Managing Large Attachments"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:120
msgid ""
"When you want to attach large attachments to an email, you may encounter "
"some limitations. When you reach the size limit set by your admin for the"
" attachments, using the \"smart links\" option, it is possible to convert"
" every attachment in Smart Links by clicking the **paperclip** icon "
"inside the composing board and choosing the \"Add public link from Files "
"option\"."
msgstr ""
"When you want to attach large attachments to an email, you may encounter "
"some limitations. When you reach the size limit set by your admin for the"
" attachments, using the \"smart links\" option, it is possible to convert"
" every attachment in Smart Links by clicking the **paperclip** icon "
"inside the composing board and choosing the \"Add public link from Files "
"option\"."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:126
msgid ""
"Afterwards, simply follow the path and select the folder inside Files, "
"where is located the file you want to send."
msgstr ""
"Afterwards, simply follow the path and select the folder inside Files, "
"where is located the file you want to send."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:131
msgid ""
"To remove an attachment from the email you are composing, simply click on"
" the **Remove** button located beneath the attachment."
msgstr ""
"To remove an attachment from the email you are composing, simply click on"
" the **Remove** button located beneath the attachment."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:134 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:167
msgid "Send an Email from a Different Account or Persona"
msgstr "Send an Email from a Different Account or Persona"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:136
msgid ""
"You can send emails from different personas or email identities while "
"composing a message."
msgstr ""
"You can send emails from different personas or email identities while "
"composing a message."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:138
msgid ""
"This feature is available if you have multiple identities or personas set"
" up."
msgstr ""
"This feature is available if you have multiple identities or personas set"
" up."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:140
msgid ""
"An email identity refers to having access to multiple accounts on the "
"|product| web client, allowing you to choose which one to send the email "
"from. Alternatively, if you have configured another persona in your "
"settings, you can send messages from it. In either case, the recipient "
"will see the email address or username aligned with the selected identity"
" or persona as the sender of the emails."
msgstr ""
"An email identity lets you choose among multiple accounts or personas in "
"the |product| web client when sending mail; the recipient sees the "
"selected address or username."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:142
msgid "To switch identities or personas, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Per commutare le identità o le persone, seguire questi passaggi:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:144
msgid ""
"Click on your email address located at the **top left corner** of the "
"composing board."
msgstr ""
"Click on your email address located at the **top left corner** of the "
"composing board."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:145
msgid "Choose your preferred identity or persona from the menu."
msgstr "Choose your preferred identity or persona from the menu."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:153 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:177
msgid "Request a Read Receipt"
msgstr "Request a Read Receipt"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:155
msgid ""
"You can configure your email to automatically request a read receipt when"
" your colleague opens your sent email."
msgstr ""
"You can configure your email to automatically request a read receipt when"
" your colleague opens your sent email."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:157
msgid ""
"Read receipts are useful to use when you need confirmation that your "
"email has been received and opened, especially in time-sensitive or "
"important communications, for accountability purposes, or in situations "
"where tracking engagement is crucial, such as in sales or marketing "
"endeavors."
msgstr ""
"Read receipts are useful to use when you need confirmation that your "
"email has been received and opened, especially in time-sensitive or "
"important communications, for accountability purposes, or in situations "
"where tracking engagement is crucial, such as in sales or marketing "
"endeavors."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:159
msgid "To request a read receipt while composing an email:"
msgstr "To request a read receipt while composing an email:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:161 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:177
msgid ""
"Click on the **three vertical dots** located within the composing board "
"at the top right corner."
msgstr ""
"Click on the **three vertical dots** located within the composing board "
"at the top right corner."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:162
msgid "Select *Request read receipt*."
msgstr "Select *Request read receipt*."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:169
msgid ""
"Please note that, in case you receive an email with a read receipt you "
"can choose between **Do not notify** or **Notify** options, so that the "
"tab will not reappear in the future. If you simply dismiss the tab by "
"clicking *x*, the pop up banner will reappear the next time you open the "
"same email."
msgstr ""
"Please note that, in case you receive an email with a read receipt you "
"can choose between **Do not notify** or **Notify** options, so that the "
"tab will not reappear in the future. If you simply dismiss the tab by "
"clicking *x*, the pop up banner will reappear the next time you open the "
"same email."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:173
msgid "Mark an Email as Important"
msgstr "Mark an Email as Important"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:175
msgid ""
"To mark the email, you are composing for your colleague as important, "
"follow these steps:"
msgstr ""
"To mark the email, you are composing for your colleague as important, "
"follow these steps:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:178
msgid "Choose Mark as important."
msgstr "Choose Mark as important."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:180
msgid ""
"Important emails will be indicated by a red upward arrow in front of the "
"subject line within your colleagues' web client."
msgstr ""
"Important emails will be indicated by a red upward arrow in front of the "
"subject line within your colleagues' web client."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:183 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:186
msgid "Save an Email as a Draft"
msgstr "Save an Email as a Draft"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:185
msgid ""
"While composing an email, if you need to send it later or finish it in "
"the future, you can save it as a draft by following these steps:"
msgstr ""
"While composing an email, if you need to send it later or finish it in "
"the future, you can save it as a draft by following these steps:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:187
msgid ""
"Click on the \"**x**\" button located at the top right corner of the "
"composing board."
msgstr ""
"Click on the \"**x**\" button located at the top right corner of the "
"composing board."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:188
msgid "A new window will open, then click on the **SAVE DRAFT** button."
msgstr "A new window will open, then click on the **SAVE DRAFT** button."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:189
msgid ""
"Your email will be saved in the **Draft** folder accessible from your "
"navigation panel."
msgstr ""
"Your email will be saved in the **Draft** folder accessible from your "
"navigation panel."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:193 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:194
msgid "Send a Drafted Email"
msgstr "Send a Drafted Email"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:195
msgid ""
"Drafted emails are accessible from the Draft folder. Here is how you can "
"access and send them:"
msgstr ""
"Drafted emails are accessible from the Draft folder. Here is how you can "
"access and send them:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:197
msgid "Click on the Draft folder in the navigation panel."
msgstr "Fare clic sulla cartella Bozza nel pannello di navigazione."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:198
msgid "Locate your desired email in the main panel."
msgstr "Locate your desired email in the main panel."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:199
msgid ""
"To edit the email before sending it, double-click on it. Alternatively, "
"you can click on it once to review it from the right side of the main "
"panel."
msgstr ""
"To edit the email before sending it, double-click on it. Alternatively, "
"you can click on it once to review it from the right side of the main "
"panel."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:200
msgid ""
"To send the email, simply click on the send button located at the top "
"right corner of the main panel."
msgstr ""
"To send the email, simply click on the send button located at the top "
"right corner of the main panel."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:207 ../../mobile_apps/mail_app.rst:106
msgid "Replying to an Email"
msgstr "Replying to an Email"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:209
msgid "To reply to an email, follow these steps:"
msgstr "To reply to an email, follow these steps:"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:211 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:231
#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:242
msgid "Locate the email in the email list."
msgstr "Locate the email in the email list."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:213
msgid "From the menu that appears, select **Reply** or **Reply all**."
msgstr "From the menu that appears, select **Reply** or **Reply all**."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:214
msgid "A new composing board will appear, allowing you to compose your reply."
msgstr "A new composing board will appear, allowing you to compose your reply."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:217
msgid "Reply and Reply All"
msgstr "Reply and Reply All"

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:219
msgid ""
"The difference between reply and reply all lies in the recipients of your"
" response. When you choose Reply, your response is directed only to the "
"sender of the original email. This is useful for responding directly to "
"the sender without involving other recipients."
msgstr ""
"The difference between reply and reply all lies in the recipients of your"
" response. When you choose Reply, your response is directed only to the "
"sender of the original email. This is useful for responding directly to "
"the sender without involving other recipients."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:221
msgid ""
"In the case of reply all, the recipients other than the original sender "
"are automatically included in the Cc (carbon copy) field of your "
"response. This means that everyone who received the original email will "
"also receive your reply."
msgstr ""
"In the case of reply all, the recipients other than the original sender "
"are automatically included in the Cc (carbon copy) field of your "
"response. This means that everyone who received the original email will "
"also receive your reply."

#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:223
msgid ""
"This option is ideal for situations where your response is relevant to "
"everyone included in the initial communication, facilitating group "
"discussions, or providing updates to multiple parties simultaneously."
msgstr ""
"This option is ideal for situations where your response is relevant to "
"everyone included in the initial communication, facilitating group "
"discussions, or providing updates to multiple parties simultaneously."

