msgid ""
"You can use your personal room to invite others for a video meeting. To "
"do so, you need to send them the link to your personal room. To obtain "
"your room's link:"
msgstr ""
"You can use your personal room to invite others for a video meeting. To "
"do so, you need to send them the link to your personal room. To obtain "
"your room's link:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:123
msgid "Select Webcam and Microphone"
msgstr "Select Webcam and Microphone"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:125
msgid ""
"Before entering a video meeting, you will be prompted to select a webcam "
"and microphone from the available options on your computer. You can also "
"choose to turn the webcam and microphone on or off before joining the "
"room. Once your selections are made, press ENTER to join the meeting."
msgstr ""
"Before entering a video meeting, you will be prompted to select a webcam "
"and microphone from the available options on your computer. You can also "
"choose to turn the webcam and microphone on or off before joining the "
"room. Once your selections are made, press ENTER to join the meeting."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:129
msgid "Enable Webcam and Microphone"
msgstr "Enable Webcam and Microphone"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:131
msgid ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can also turn your webcam or "
"microphone on or off. Here is how: Toggle the microphone or camera icon "
"on the bottom bar inside the meeting room. If you do not see the bottom "
"bar, simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it "
"will appear."
msgstr ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can also turn your webcam or "
"microphone on or off. Here is how: Toggle the microphone or camera icon "
"on the bottom bar inside the meeting room. If you do not see the bottom "
"bar, simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it "
"will appear."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:133
msgid ""
"During a video meeting, you have the chance to blur your background. "
"Simply click on the arrow icon in the camera button, and then choose the "
"option Apply Blur Effect."
msgstr ""
"During a video meeting, you have the chance to blur your background. "
"Simply click on the arrow icon in the camera button, and then choose the "
"option Apply Blur Effect."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:135
msgid ""
"You also have the chance to choose a specific background image. Click on "
"the arrow icon in the camera button, and then choose the option Apply "
"Background Image. You can upload your own image or choose one from the "
"available options."
msgstr ""
"You also have the chance to choose a specific background image. Click on "
"the arrow icon in the camera button, and then choose the option Apply "
"Background Image. You can upload your own image or choose one from the "
"available options."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:139
msgid "Recording a Video Meeting"
msgstr "Recording a Video Meeting"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:141
msgid "When you are in a video meeting and want to record it:"
msgstr "When you are in a video meeting and want to record it:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:143
msgid "Click the **arrow button** on the left side to open the chat box."
msgstr "Click the blue button in the bottom left corner to open the chat box."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:144
msgid ""
"In the chat box, click the **downward arrow** next to the *Recording* "
"section at the top."
msgstr ""
"Clicca sull'icona della freccia verso il basso situata accanto alla "
"sezione Tag per aprire l'elenco dei tag."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:145
msgid "Click **START RECORDING** to begin recording."
msgstr "Click **START RECORDING** to begin recording."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:146
msgid "To stop the recording, click **STOP RECORDING**."
msgstr "Under the **Recording** section, click **START**."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:148
msgid ""
"Whether the recording is stopped by the person who started it or by "
"another **moderator**, the file will always be saved into the *Files* of "
"the person who started the recording."
msgstr ""
"Whether the recording is stopped by the person who started it or by "
"another **moderator**, the file will always be saved into the *Files* of "
"the person who started the recording."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:149
msgid "A popup will appear asking you to enter a **name for the recording file**."
msgstr "Una finestra di dialogo apparirà. Inserisci un nome per il nuovo tag."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:152
msgid ""
"If all meeting participants (including the person who started the "
"recording) leave the meeting, the system will automatically stop the "
"recording and save the file in the *Files* of the person who clicked "
"**START RECORDING**."
msgstr ""
"If all meeting participants (including the person who started the "
"recording) leave the meeting, the system will automatically stop the "
"recording and save the file in the *Files* of the person who clicked "
"**START RECORDING**."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:158
msgid "Recording Saved Notifications"
msgstr "Silenzia le notifiche di una chat"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:160
msgid ""
"When a Chats meeting recording is successfully saved to Files, the "
"recording initiator receives an automatic notification in the Files "
"Notifications widget. The notification is displayed as “<recording name> "
"saved in <folder name>” and includes the destination folder path, so the "
"recording can be found quickly in Files."
msgstr ""
"When a Chats meeting recording is successfully saved to Files, the "
"recording initiator receives an automatic notification in the Files "
"Notifications widget. The notification is displayed as “<recording name> "
"saved in <folder name>” and includes the destination folder path, so the "
"recording can be found quickly in Files."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:163
msgid ""
"This notification is system-generated and uses the system avatar "
"(settings icon) to distinguish it from user activity. The feature is "
"enabled by default and requires no administrative configuration."
msgstr ""
"This notification is system-generated and uses the system avatar "
"(settings icon) to distinguish it from user activity. The feature is "
"enabled by default and requires no administrative configuration."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:170
msgid "Adding New Members to a Video Meeting"
msgstr "Adding New Members to a Video Meeting"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:172
msgid ""
"To add new members to an ongoing video meeting, you need to send them the"
" link to access the room. Here is how:"
msgstr ""
"To add new members to an ongoing video meeting, you need to send them the"
" link to access the room. Here is how:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:174
msgid "Make sure you are in the meeting."
msgstr "Make sure you are in the meeting."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:175
msgid "Copy the URL of the page from the address bar of your browser."
msgstr "Copy the URL of the page from the address bar of your browser."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:177
msgid ""
"This will copy the link to access your room to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"Paste, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or command+V "
"on macOS."
msgstr ""
"This will copy the link to access your room to your clipboard. You can "
"paste it anywhere (such as in a chat) by right-clicking and selecting "
"Paste, or by using the keyboard shortcut CTRL+V on Windows or command+V "
"on macOS."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:180
msgid "Accessing Chat History During a Video Meeting"
msgstr "Accessing Chat History During a Video Meeting"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:182
msgid ""
"To access the chat box of the room where you are having the video "
"meeting, simply click the arrow button on the left side to open the chat "
"box."
msgstr ""
"To access the chat box of the room where you are having the video "
"meeting, simply click the arrow button on the left side to open the chat "
"box."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:185
msgid "Sharing Screen During a Video Meeting"
msgstr "Sharing Screen During a Video Meeting"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:187
msgid ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can share your screen with "
"attendees. Here is how: Click the screen icon on the bottom bar inside "
"the meeting room. If you do not see the bottom bar, simply move your "
"mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it will appear. You have "
"three options to choose from: •       Your browser tab. •       A "
"specific window. •       Entire screen. Select the desired option and "
"then click Share."
msgstr ""
"When you are in a video meeting, you can share your screen with "
"attendees. Here is how: Click the screen icon on the bottom bar inside "
"the meeting room. If you do not see the bottom bar, simply move your "
"mouse cursor to the bottom of the screen, and it will appear. You have "
"three options to choose from: •       Your browser tab. •       A "
"specific window. •       Entire screen. Select the desired option and "
"then click Share."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:195
msgid "Maximizing Video Meeting Screen"
msgstr "Maximizing Video Meeting Screen"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:197
msgid ""
"To maximize the video meeting screen, click on the icon with arrows "
"inside located on the bottom bar. If you do not see the bottom bar inside"
" the meeting room, simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the "
"screen, and it will appear."
msgstr ""
"To maximize the video meeting screen, click on the icon with arrows "
"inside located on the bottom bar. If you do not see the bottom bar inside"
" the meeting room, simply move your mouse cursor to the bottom of the "
"screen, and it will appear."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:200
msgid "Cinema Mode Fullscreen Feature"
msgstr "Cinema Mode Fullscreen Feature"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:202
msgid ""
"Cinema Mode provides an optimized viewing experience during meetings, "
"allowing you to focus on shared content or participants with an immersive"
" fullscreen display."
msgstr ""
"Cinema Mode provides an optimized viewing experience during meetings, "
"allowing you to focus on shared content or participants with an immersive"
" fullscreen display."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:204
msgid ""
"This feature enables you to: * View meetings in Cinema Mode for a more "
"engaging experience * Activate fullscreen mode to eliminate interface "
"distractions * Optimize display during presentations or collaborative "
"sessions"
msgstr ""
"This feature enables you to: * View meetings in Cinema Mode for a more "
"engaging experience * Activate fullscreen mode to eliminate interface "
"distractions * Optimize display during presentations or collaborative "
"sessions"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:209
msgid ""
"To use the Cinema Mode and fullscreen features, follow these steps: * "
"Join a meeting: Enter an existing meeting * Switch to Cinema view: In the"
" view options, select \"Cinema\" mode to optimize the display layout * "
"Enable fullscreen: Activate fullscreen mode to maximize the viewing area "
"and remove interface elements"
msgstr ""
"To use the Cinema Mode and fullscreen features, follow these steps: * "
"Join a meeting: Enter an existing meeting * Switch to Cinema view: In the"
" view options, select \"Cinema\" mode to optimize the display layout * "
"Enable fullscreen: Activate fullscreen mode to maximize the viewing area "
"and remove interface elements"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:214
msgid ""
"The full-screen mode now automatically hides the sidebar and carousel in "
"cinema view, and hides the sidebar in other views. When full screen is "
"activated in cinema view, left panel and carousel will be closed."
msgstr ""
"The full-screen mode now automatically hides the sidebar and carousel in "
"cinema view, and hides the sidebar in other views. When full screen is "
"activated in cinema view, left panel and carousel will be closed."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:217
msgid "Raise Hand Feature"
msgstr "Raise Hand Feature"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:219
msgid ""
"The Raise Hand feature allows meeting participants to signal their desire"
" to speak through a structured queue system, promoting organized "
"discussions and better meeting flow."
msgstr ""
"The Raise Hand feature allows meeting participants to signal their desire"
" to speak through a structured queue system, promoting organized "
"discussions and better meeting flow."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:221
msgid "How It Works for Participants:"
msgstr "How It Works for Participants:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:223
msgid "Raise hand to join speaking queue"
msgstr "Raise hand to join speaking queue"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:224
msgid "View real-time queue showing order, avatars, and usernames"
msgstr "View real-time queue showing order, avatars, and usernames"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:225
msgid "Receive audio notifications when others raise hands"
msgstr "Receive audio notifications when others raise hands"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:226
msgid "Hand automatically lowers when speaking begins"
msgstr "Hand automatically lowers when speaking begins"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:228
msgid "Moderators"
msgstr "Moderators"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:230
msgid "Access dedicated queue management panel"
msgstr "Access dedicated queue management panel"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:231
msgid "Lower individual hands or clear entire queue"
msgstr "Lower individual hands or clear entire queue"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:232
msgid "Actions sync across all moderators in real-time"
msgstr "Actions sync across all moderators in real-time"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:234
msgid ""
"This feature streamlines meeting participation by providing clear "
"speaking order while giving moderators effective queue management tools."
msgstr ""
"This feature streamlines meeting participation by providing clear "
"speaking order while giving moderators effective queue management tools."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:236
msgid "To activate the Raise Hand feature during a video meeting:"
msgstr "To activate the Raise Hand feature during a video meeting:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:238
msgid "Click the hand icon on the bottom bar inside the meeting room."
msgstr "Click the hand icon on the bottom bar inside the meeting room."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:239
msgid "When you will start speaking, your hand will be automatically lowered."
msgstr "When you will start speaking, your hand will be automatically lowered."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:240
msgid "If you want to lower your hand manually, simply click the hand icon again."
msgstr "If you want to lower your hand manually, simply click the hand icon again."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:241
msgid ""
"If you are a moderator, you can also lower the hands of other "
"participants by clicking on the hand icon next to their name in the "
"Participants section of the chat box."
msgstr ""
"If you are a moderator, you can also lower the hands of other "
"participants by clicking on the hand icon next to their name in the "
"Participants section of the chat box."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:244
msgid "Muting Participants During a Video Meeting"
msgstr "Muting Participants During a Video Meeting"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:246
msgid ""
"As the moderator of a meeting room, you can mute an attendee's microphone"
" individually. To do so, simply hover your cursor over the video feed of "
"the attendee and click on the microphone icon located at the corner of "
"their video feed."
msgstr ""
"As the moderator of a meeting room, you can mute an attendee's microphone"
" individually. To do so, simply hover your cursor over the video feed of "
"the attendee and click on the microphone icon located at the corner of "
"their video feed."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:248 ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:268
msgid "Click the arrow button on the left side to open the chat box."
msgstr "Click the arrow button on the left side to open the chat box."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:249 ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:269
msgid ""
"Click the downward arrow next to the Participants section located at the "
"top of the chat box."
msgstr ""
"Click the downward arrow next to the Participants section located at the "
"top of the chat box."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:250
msgid "Click the microphone icon next to the participant’s name."
msgstr "Click the microphone icon next to the participant’s name."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:251
msgid "Click MUTE FOR ALL to confirm."
msgstr "Click MUTE FOR ALL to confirm."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:256
msgid "To delete a meeting room:"
msgstr "To delete a meeting room:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:260
msgid "Click the trash icon beside the name of the room you want to delete."
msgstr "Click the trash icon beside the name of the room you want to delete."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:261
msgid "Click DELETE to confirm."
msgstr "Click DELETE to confirm."

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:264
msgid "Adding Moderators to a Room"
msgstr "Adding Moderators to a Room"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:266
msgid "To add a moderator to a meeting room:"
msgstr "To add a moderator to a meeting room:"

#: ../../videomeeting/toc.rst:270
msgid "Click the crown icon next to the participant’s name."
msgstr "Click the crown icon next to the participant’s name."

